{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legalise use of electric scooters on public highways for driving licence holders",
        "additional_details": "We believe there is no reason for private e-scooters to still be illegal when e-bikes are legal to ride.\r\n \r\nAt least one study has found that the incident rate for e-Scooters is lower than for bicycles, and e-scooters provide a clean and efficient mode of transportation.\r\n \r\nLiving in suburban areas I find myself using a car for shortish journeys when I could use an e-Scooter. This not only would save on pollution, but also congestion on already busy roads.\r\n \r\nThese scooters are already a success in many parts of Europe so let\u2019s join the future and clean up our roads/air.\r\n",
        "background": "We believe electric scooters are an integral part of the future for short distance travel and should be made legal to use on public roads for those holding a provisional/full UK driving licence.",
